06/06/2006
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- The OSCE Mission to Serbia and Montenegro and the Standing Conference of Towns and Municipalities announced on Monday (5 June) that they have drafted a guidebook for the Municipal Councils for Interethnic Relations. The book aims to establish tolerance in ethnically mixed municipalities and to encourage understanding and collaboration in those communities. The guidebook also contains information on the ethnic composition of Serbia and on domestic and international legislation related to protection of minority rights. (OSCE Web site, Tanjug - 05/06/06) 
